U.K. Stocks Declined for a second
day as shares of mining companies retreated.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index lost 0.3 percent to 6,367.97
at 8:22 a.m. in  London . Rio Tinto Group was the biggest drag on
the gauge, falling 2.7 percent to 2,997.5 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
